 of politics to Richard Rorty, John Rawls, and Judith Butler, Barkeroffers a major reassessment of contemporary political theory and a fresh perspective on the most urgent challenges facing democratic politics.Derek W. M. Barker is a program officer at the Kettering Foundation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aCitizenshipxPhilosophyxElectronic books. 0aCitizenshipxPhilosophy. 0aGreek drama (Tragedy)xPolitical aspects. 0aPolitical sciencexHistoryxTo 1500xGreece. 0aPolitical sciencexPhilosophyxHistory. 0aPolitical sciencezGreecexHistoryyTo 1500. 4aPhilosophy : Ancient Greek Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Hegel. 4aPhilosophy : History of Philosophy. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Theory. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978079147740340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791477403423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791477403/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles